{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, human evaluation is characterized as a non-automated approach.",
    "The approach of code evaluation entails the extraction of responses from LLMs, referencing authentic annotations, and utilizing code to statistically compute predefined evaluation metrics.",
    "The efficacy of LLMs is consequently gauged through the numerical values of these metrics.",
    "Prominent evaluation metrics include accuracy, F1 score, BLEU (Papineni et al, 2002), ROUGE (Lin, 2004), Exact Match 60, Pearson correlation coefficient 61, among others.",
    "For instance, accuracy can be employed in classification tasks to appraise the precision of LLMs' classifications."
  ]
}